calculations

Class BmiCalc

  • java.lang.Object
    • calculations.BmiCalc

  • public class BmiCalc
extends java.lang.Object
    This class calculates the body mass index (BMI). There are two different calculations: one for metric units & one for imperial units. Both formulas use the given weight and height in in order to calculate the BMI.
    Version:
    11/7/18
    Author:
    Spencer Keeton

      • feetToInches

        public double feetToInches(double ft,
                           double in)
        This method converts feet into inches. This method is a helper method to convert feet into inches, due to the imperial formula for BMI only using inches as a height measurement.
        Parameters:
        ft - The feet component of the imperial measured height.
        in - The inches component of imperial measured height.
        Returns:
        plc_hld + in; The amount of inches that the feet were converted plus the amount of inches provided.

      • bmiMetric

        public double bmiMetric()
        This method calculates the BMI using the metric formula. The metric formula for calculating BMI is: BMI = weight(kg) / height^2(m^2)
        Returns:
        bmi_m The BMI result for metric calculations.

      • bmiImperial

        public double bmiImperial()
        This method calculates the BMI using the imperial formula. The imperial formula for calculating BMI is: BMI = weight(lbs) * 703 / (height^2(in^2))
        Returns:
        bmi_i The BMI result for imperial calculations.
